item.description:
@b00mz1029 wrote:

Theres something wrong with the newest jdk that doesn’t let you jar with it, so how do I change it so it compiles with my oldest java? this is my compilers run.bat

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

item.title: Pi probs
item.dc:creator: @Loveandpower Loveandpower
item.description:
@Loveandpower wrote:

The webclient error first:

major minor error is thrown when you run a batch file that is using an older java than it was compiled on. This can be resolved by recompiling the regular client with the newest java then playing. Then you can rejar it.

@Loveandpower wrote:

what does the error say when you click for details?

Also, to add items correctly to a client, you need to add the model, add the ints, add a proper model header, and add the item into item.cfg. If you have the correct item but a different model is displayed use a datviewer and make sure the model is what it’s supposed to be.
